adverbs.description: unmeetly (comparative more unmeetly, superlative most unmeetly)

entries.meaning: In an unmeet way; unbecomingly. [from 16th c.]
examples: Yet there are noble passages in his later poems: and even the latest have their own peculiar charm of serenity and kindliness,—a tranquil sunset, as it were, succeeding not unmeetly to the fiery splendours of his noontide course.
